item.title: My 562 RunServer.bat is broke :/ could someone help me?
item.dc:creator: @Haydnz1234 Haydnz1234
item.description:
@Haydnz1234 wrote:

darkd3ad:

I have tried to remember how to fix this all night and for some reason i can’t its been a min since i have coded. I’m trying to run a 562 server and idr how to fix this problem any suggestions?? [URL=http://imageshack.us/photo/my-images/818/serverproblem.png/]

In your run.bat, it probably should say something like this:
“C:/Program Files/Java/jre7/bin/java.exe” - Whatever it says if it’s similar to that follow the path (C drive>Program files>Java>JRE NAME HERE) and change whatever is different, such as change the jre7 to jre6 or whatever you have.

If not then maybe it looks like this:
“C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.7.0_11\bin/java.exe” - Whatever it says, yet again if it’s similar to that follow the path (go to C drive>Program files>Java>JDK NAME HERE and change it to what the file name is… Here’s an example

I’m using JDK 1.6.0_23 and in my run.bat it says “C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.7.0_11\bin/java.exe” - I would go to C:\Program Files\Java and see what JDK file there is… then i’d go back to my run.bat and change the “C:\Program Files\Java[b]jdk1.7.0_11[/b]\bin/java.exe” to jdk1.6.0_23

No problemo…
